Well, turkeys make use of tall trees to increase the distance between ground-dwelling predators and themselves. Not only does sleeping in trees get turkey off the ground and away from predators, but roosting turkeys also have a great line of sight to detect approaching predators.And although tall trees are must for turkey populations, turkeys are not selective with regard to specific tree species.ell, turkeys make use of tall trees to increase the distance between ground-dwelling predators and themselves. Not only does sleeping in trees get turkey off the ground and away from predators, but roosting turkeys also have a great line of sight to detect approaching predators.
